<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="487" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,222,535]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,402,427]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">Remarks.</emphasis>
no specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[558,651,402,427]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">Madeira</collectingRegion>
could be located in natural history collections. 
<bibRefCitation box="[1216,1436,402,427]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" refId="ref27192" refString="Wirtz, P., Fricke, R. &amp; Biscoito, M. J. (2008) The coastal fishes of Madeira Island - new records and an annotated check-list. Zootaxa, 1715, 1 - 26." type="journal article">
Wirtz 
<emphasis box="[1290,1343,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">et al</emphasis>
. (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
mention that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bonnaterre" baseAuthorityYear="1788" box="[304,439,438,463]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Myliobatidae" genus="Mobula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mobular">
<emphasis box="[304,439,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">M. mobular</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sightings may eventually be 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[780,949,439,462]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Myliobatidae" genus="Mobula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tarapacana">
<emphasis box="[780,949,439,462]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">M. tarapacana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A similar situation seems to occur in the Canary Islands (
<bibRefCitation box="[332,522,474,499]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" refId="ref21208" refString="Brito, A., Pascual, P. J., Falcon, J. M., Sancho, A. &amp; Gonzalez, G. (2002) Peces de las Islas Canarias: catalogo comentado e ilustrado. Francisco Lemus, La Laguna, 419 pp." type="book">
Brito 
<emphasis box="[399,448,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">et al</emphasis>
. 2002
</bibRefCitation>
). Until a solid proof of the occurrence of this species in Madeiran waters appears, we consider the presence of this species as in need of confirmation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
